    <fr:title text="How to code your own type theory">How to code your own type theory</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Reference</fr:taxon>
    <fr:meta name="video">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DEj-_k2Nx6o</fr:meta>
    <fr:meta name="venue">Colloquium, HoTTEST Summer School 2022</fr:meta>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>There is a considerable distance between the formal rules of type theory and the code that you must write in order to animate them as a running program. In this colloquium, you will learn the basic techniques of type theoretic implementation in the OCaml programming language, including the representation of syntax as well as type-directed conversion.</fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
